{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:titus.2",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "titus",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "Titus 2",
    "summary": "Source text for Titus 2 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:1",
      "text": "But speak thou the things that become sound doctrine:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:2",
      "text": "That the aged men be sober, chaste, prudent, sound in faith, in love, in patience.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:3",
      "text": "The aged women, in like manner, in holy attire, not false accusers, not given to much wine, teaching well:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:4",
      "text": "That they may teach the young women to be wise, to love their husbands, to love their children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:5",
      "text": "To be discreet, chaste, sober, having a care of the house, gentle, obedient to their husbands: that the word of God be not blasphemed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:6",
      "text": "Young men, in like manner, exhort that they be sober.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:7",
      "text": "In all things shew thyself an example of good works, in doctrine, in integrity, in gravity,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:8",
      "text": "The sound word that can not be blamed: that he who is on the contrary part may be afraid, having no evil to say of us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:9",
      "text": "Exhort servants to be obedient to their masters: in all things pleasing, not gainsaying:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:10",
      "text": "Not defrauding, but in all things shewing good fidelity, that they may adorn the doctrine of God our Saviour in all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:11",
      "text": "For the grace of God our Saviour hath appeared to all men:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:12",
      "text": "Instructing us, that, denying ungodliness and worldly desires, we should live soberly and justly and godly in this world,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:13",
      "text": "Looking for the blessed hope and coming of the glory of the great God and our Saviour Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:14",
      "text": "Who gave himself for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity and might cleanse to himself a people acceptable, a pursuer of good works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:titus.2.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:15",
      "text": "These things speak and exhort and rebuke with all authority. Let no man despise thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
